6 An Act relating to employment benefits; amending 40
O.S. 2021, Section 2-417, as amended by Section 1,
7 Chapter 309, O.S.L. 2024 (40 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
2-417), which relates to disqualification; modifying
8 conditions for disqualification for certain benefits;
specifying acceptable work search actions; updating
9 statutory language; and providing an effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 40 O.S. 2021, Section 2-417, as
14 amended by Section 1, Chapter 309, O.S.L. 2024 (40 O.S. Supp. 2025,
15 Section 2-417), is amended to read as follows:
16 Section 2-417.
17 SEEK AND ACCEPT WORK - WEEK OF OCCURRENCE DISQUALIFICATION.
18 A. An individual shall be disqualified to receive benefits for
19 each week in which the individual shall have failed to do any of the
20 following:
21 1. Diligently search for suitable employment at a pay rate
22 generally available in that area of the state in keeping with his or
23 her prior experience, education and training; or
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1277 Page 1

1 2. Make application for the minimum number of weekly work
2 search efforts as required by the Oklahoma Employment Security
3 Commission; or
4 3. Present oneself as an applicant for employment in a manner
5 designed to encourage favorable employment consideration Conduct
6 three weekly search actions, or more if required by the Oklahoma
7 Employment Security Commission based on economic or geographic
8 factors.
9 B. Acceptable work search actions shall be determined by the
10 Commission and shall include, but not be limited to:
11 1. Submitting a resume to an employer;
12 2. Completing and submitting a job application to an employer;
13 3. Attending and completing an interview with an employer;
14 4. Participating in a work-related networking event sponsored
15 by the Commission such as a job club or fair, industry association
16 event, or networking group;
17 5. Participating in reemployment services offered to the
18 claimant by the Commission or any other state employment service;
19 6. Participating in a volunteer training opportunity likely to
20 lead to paid employment;
21 7. Taking a civil service exam for work in a government agency;
22 8. Developing or uploading a complete resume in the state’s
23 employment service system for the purpose of obtaining employment;
24 or
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1277 Page 2

1 9. Any other work search activities prescribed by the
2 Commission.
3 B. C. The requirements of subsection A of this section shall be
4 waived if the individual has been summoned to appear for jury duty
5 before any court of the United States or of any state. The waiver
6 will shall continue for as long as the individual remains on jury
7 duty pursuant to the original summons.
8 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
9 Passed the Senate the 9th day of March, 2026.
